## API Reference

### Dialog / Dialog.Content

The main dialog container that renders the modal overlay and popup.

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `size` | `"base" \| "sm" \| "lg" \| "xl"` | `"base"` | Dialog width variant. |
| `container` | `HTMLElement \| string` | — | Portal target. |
| `id` | `string` | — | Dialog content ID. |
| `style` | `string` | — | Inline style string. |
| `class` | `string` | — | Additional classes. |
| `children` | `Snippet` | — | Dialog content. |

### Dialog.Root

Controls the open state of the dialog. Does not render its own HTML element.

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `open` | `boolean` | `false` | Open state. Bind with `bind:open`. |
| `onOpenChange` | `(open: boolean) => void` | — | Called when the open state changes. |
| `role` | `"dialog" \| "alertdialog"` | `"dialog"` | ARIA role. Use `"alertdialog"` for destructive or confirmation flows. |
| `disablePointerDismissal` | `boolean` | `false` | Prevent outside pointer interactions from closing the dialog. |
| `children` | `Snippet` | — | Trigger and content. |

### Dialog.Trigger

A button that opens the dialog when clicked.

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `children` | `Snippet` | — | Trigger content. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Disable the trigger. |
| `id` | `string` | — | Trigger ID. |
| `class` | `string` | — | Additional classes. |

### Dialog.Close

A button that closes the dialog when clicked.

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `children` | `Snippet` | — | Close button content. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Disable the close button. |
| `id` | `string` | — | Close button ID. |
| `class` | `string` | — | Additional classes. |

### Dialog.Title and Dialog.Description

Use `Dialog.Title` to label the dialog and `Dialog.Description` to describe it for assistive technologies.

### Dialog.Header and Dialog.Footer

Layout helpers for common dialog header and footer arrangements. They accept standard `HTMLDivElement` attributes and `children`.
